text: 78. Regression estimates of the expenditure on different commodities attributable consisting of childless couples (both under 55) and couples with different numbers of children were given for 1952-56 in Table 39 of the Annual Report for 1956. The younger childless couples are broadly comparable in age and family income with the family households, so that differences in food expenditure may be associated with the presence of children.
